<section id="about">
<h2>About Me</h2>
<p>I am Raima Sing, a recent graduate with an Integrated MSc (2019-24) in Life
Sciences from the National Institute of Science Education and Research (NISER),
Bhubaneswar, India. My Master's thesis focused on investigating the role of cold-sensitive
TRP ion channels in microglial function and iron homeostasis.
I am currently working as a project student investigating how TRP channels
regulate microglial iron homeostasis and its possible role in neurodegeneration. I aspire to
conduct transformative research that improves the lives of individuals affected by chronic
disorders while advancing societal health and well-being.</p>
</section>
<section id="Schlorship">
<h2>Funding</h2>
<p>I was the recipient of the prestigious DISHA Scholarship (2019-24) from the
Department of Atomic Energy (DAE), the government of INDIA</p>
</section>
<section id="research">
<h2>Research Experience</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Master's Thesis:</strong> Explored the role of TRPM8 ion
channels in microglial function and iron homeostasis.</li>
<li><strong>Project Student:</strong> NISER, Bhubaneswar, India (06/2024 –
Present)
<ul>
<li><strong>Supervisor:</strong> Prof. (Dr). Chandan Goswami</li>
<li><strong>Project 1:</strong> Investigating the role of TRP in
neurodegeneration.
<ul>
<li><strong>Key findings:</strong> Modulation of TRP channels
regulates microglial iron homeostasis.</li>
<li><strong>Techniques used:</strong> Cell culture, Live-cell
Confocal microscopy, Immunocytochemistry, Optimized MTT assays, and Image
analysis.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Project 2:</strong> Characterizing endogenous TRPM8
activator.
<ul>
<li><strong>Key findings:</strong> Ca²⁺ imaging using GCaMP
shows the endogenous activator is functional in neuronal and microglial cells and impacts
organelle functions.</li>
<li><strong>Techniques used:</strong> Cell culture, Confocal
microscopy, Instant Ca2+ imaging, Transformation and transfection, and Image
analysis.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Summer Internship:</strong> Advance Centre for Treatment
Research and Education in Cancer (ACTREC), Mumbai, India (5/2020 – 07/2020)
<ul>
<li><strong>Supervisor:</strong> Prof. (Dr). Jayant Sastri Goda</li>
<li>Could not continue due to COVID-19 pandemic.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>R.K. University, Rajkot, India (07/2020 – 09/2020)</strong>
<ul>
<li><strong>Supervisor:</strong> Dr. Vijay Kumar</li>
<li><strong>Project:</strong> Conducted in-depth research on probiotics
and prebiotics, enhancing understanding of gut microbiota.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Winter Internship:</strong> NISER, Bhubaneswar, India
(12/2022–01/2023 & 12/2023–01/2024)
<ul>
<li><strong>Supervisor:</strong> Prof. (Dr). Chandan Goswami</li>
<li><strong>Project 1:</strong> Explored the role of thermosensitive ion
channels during cholesterol depletion in activated and resting microglial cells.
<ul>
<li><strong>Key findings:</strong> TRPM8 localization in lipid
raft is dependent on membrane cholesterol level.</li>
<li><strong>Techniques used:</strong> Cell culture, Confocal
microscopy, Hydrogels, Image analysis and statistics, IF staining, cholesterol reduction assay,
Bacterial transformation, and transfection.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Project 2:</strong> Studied modulation of thermosensitive
TRP ion channels using hydrogels in neuronal cells.
<ul>
<li><strong>Key findings:</strong> Modulation of TRP ion
channels affects organelle function in the presence of hydrogel.</li>
<li><strong>Techniques used:</strong> 2D cell culture using
hydrogels, Confocal microscopy, Image analysis and statistics.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</section>
